comments.body:
@ksstott is basically right. @types/webpack@4 needs to stay on DT to keep receiving updates, but updated plugins like this one need to be able to refer to webpack@5, which ships its own types.

The solution is for updated plugins to add package.json like you'd expect (so that the plugin has the correct dependencies when installed), but also use path mappings so that the DT tests resolve to a local copy of webpack@5. The tsconfig doesn't ship to npm, so the path mapping is just to make DT compile correctly.

This is a one-off for webpack for now, and I haven't figured out how or where to document it.
